--- !u!114 &8109120333061929774
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 427269962567425283}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Sector 44AL1 - Incident Report \r\nResponding Superior: Dr. Yaemil\r\nTo:
    Higher Command, Sector 13AO\r\n\r\n    I regret to inform Sector 13AO that there
    has been, yet again, another stir in individuals who are upset with our lack
    of motivation to weaponize organic compound VELLIUM.\r\n\r\n    They seem to
    lack the ability to understand that we have no wish to become the very things
    we escaped from. Perhaps they are too young to remember, or their core kin units
    hold beliefs that go against the Council, but there is tension rising in Sector
    44AL1.\r\n\r\n    While studying the organic compound V, an entry-level energy
    reader, Ryrne proceeded to initiate an argument with their lab counterpart, Flitz.
    After careful investigation of both parties to discover the unbiased truth, it
    seems that Ryrne wished to attempt to supercharge the compound. His reasoning
    was: \u201CTo know what it\u2019s capable of.\u201D\r\n\r\n    As this is his
    third infraction this moon cycle, he is on probationary work under a constant
    supervisor to prevent any possible accidents from happening. Ryrne must also
    complete mandatory retraining regarding our goals and how to safely handle the
    organic compound.\r\n\r\n    Discussing with Flitz led me to learning that Ryrne
    and others (not named) wish to see what the compound is capable of. As a result
    of their curious nature, I have stationed more security around sectors that deal
    with RAW VELLIUM. \r\n\r\n    I do not know if he has the guts to attempt to
    learn what it can do on his own, but I do not feel comfortable dealing with this
    in a lax manner. \r\n\r\n    Going forward, I will watch over 44AL1 better and
    highly encourage other sectors dealing with VELLIUM or VELLITE to do the same.\r\n\r\n   
    Sincerely, \r\n    Dr. Yaemil"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d8d83447fa4043f4dbc45b3e589dbb00, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -1945405297897605184, guid: d8d83447fa4043f4dbc45b3e589dbb00, type: 2}
