--- !u!114 &5486698403704356295
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 4703117997688220754}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Sector 44AL2 - Incident Report\r\nResponding Superior: Dr. Fulsi\r\nTo:
    Higher Command, Sector 13AO\r\n\r\n\tDuring the middle of last night's moon change,
    it came to my attention that someone initiated an extraction process. I went
    to investigate immediately, but by the time I arrived, we seemed to be missing
    valuable VELLITE samples. Upon watching surveillance footage, multiple people
    infiltrated an inactive lab to retrieve the organic compound from a locked safebox.
    \r\n\r\n\tAmong these people was Ryrne, but we\u2019re actively working on identifying
    the four others and where they got their credentials from to access the high-level
    security containment. Unfortunately, I believe there may be more than these five
    people working towards some . . . nefarious goal. By the Council, I pray that
    they are simply too curious for their own good. \r\n\r\n\tThough . . . I don\u2019t
    think this is the last time this is going to happen. There have been circulating
    reports of people poking around extraction sites, and things going missing during
    lab inventory checks. I just . . . I have a bad feeling, Sector 13AO. There\u2019s
    no other way for me to put it. \r\n\r\n\tTo put it plainly, I am worried for
    our safety. I do not know what they wish to do, just that they fantasize about
    weapons in the name of protection. Dr. Yaemil tried to redirect them to put their
    spirit into something helpful, but they resisted. Spoke with poison in their
    minds about needing weapons to protect us, to take us further. How we could be
    stronger with them than without them. It was like they were overtaken by the
    lust for violence.\r\n\t\r\n\tI fear for what this means for us if we can\u2019t
    stop them. Please take my warnings with the utmost seriousness; it\u2019s dire.
    This can\u2019t be ignored any longer.\r\n\r\n\r\n\tBy the Council, get us through
    this.\r\n\tDr. Fulsi\r\n"
