--- !u!114 &1827309985624879322
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 7502072112226317605}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Catastrophic Accident Report\r\nResponder: Dr. Yaemil\r\nTo: High Council,
    000\r\n\r\n    I regret to inform the Council, but there was a superior weapon
    launched at high star today into the large astral body that orbits around our
    current planet. The Eclipse Body. \r\n\r\n    I am of the belief that Ryrne and
    those who follow the same ideals are behind it. See our previous reports from
    Sector 44AL, but they have been problematic for many moons with no response to
    reinforcement, treatment, or punishment. \r\n\r\n    The Eclipse Body has fractured
    and is in many pieces. We are unsure how this will affect the eclipse or our
    society going forward. We have set up a rotational observation committee dedicated
    to observing the orbital body to ensure that we witness everything that will
    come as a result of this change. \r\n\r\n    One of the speakers from Sector
    896A will be doing a broadcast later today explaining the events that have transpired
    to put public unease, hopefully, at rest.\r\n\r\n    From current observation,
    EB1 has broken into many smaller fragments. Our current worry is that EB1 will
    now have a prolonged eclipse period, dampening the potency of the VELLIUM used
    throughout the city. Along with this, concerns regarding orbital patterns are
    being considered as well. \r\n\r\n    The weapon seemed to be a high-powered
    projectile that utilized heat energy and combustion to send it far out of our
    atmosphere to hit EB1. There was a shockwave as a result of the weapon firing,
    but it\u2019s believed there\u2019s only minor damage to buildings close to the
    firing site. \r\n\r\n    The weapon has not been found despite our team's best
    efforts to mobilize and find the firing site as quickly as possible after the
    shot was fired. We are working on tracking it to confiscate it, but we do not
    know where Ryrne or the rest of his party is. When they are located, they will
    also be taken in for questioning and punishment. \r\n\r\n    I will continue
    to send in frequent reports as we discover more information regarding this incident.
    I apologize for it getting this far despite our best efforts to stop it. \r\n\r\n   
    Sincerely,\r\n    Dr. Yaemil\r\n"
