  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Advisory Report: Biological Effects of Vellum - Dr. Luum\r\n245 Sun\n\r\n   
    Vellium, identified by its violet hue, is producing destabilizing effects across
    multiple forms of life. Disruptions represent a direct threat to ecological stability,
    warranting immediate precautionary measures.\n\r\nObservations\r\n    - Animals:
    Subjects displayed uneven enlargement of anatomy, violet discoloration of fur,
    and wings. Showed aggression and reduced predator avoidance.\n\r\n    - Insects:
    Subjects displayed growth far outside studied ranges. They abandon swarming patterns,
    becoming erratic.\n\r\n    - Flora: Vegetation developed enlarged stalks, abnormal
    vascular tissue, and streaked purple pigmentation.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnalysis\n\r\n   
    The changes in organic material suggest that Vellium acts on core biological
    regulators of growth and pigmentation. In fauna, the effect extends into neurological
    pathways, disturbing instinctual order and driving unpredictable aggression.
    Such alterations compromise predator-prey relationships and the cohesion of insect
    colonies, posing risks of ecological collapse.\r\n\nImplications and Recommendations\r\n\n   
    Unchecked spread of Vellium could destabilize ecosystems and endanger our community.
    Until it's understood, treat it as a significant ecological hazard. It is recommended
    that:\r\n\n    - Vellium remains confined to secure laboratory conditions.\r\n\r\n   
    - Monitoring Zones are established around potential contamination sites.\r\n\r\n   
    - Research prioritizes the neurological and behavioural impacts on fauna.\r\n"
